# Rust
/target/
**/target/
Cargo.lock.bak

# OpenOrbis PS4 Toolchain, cloned by the user, not vendored (see README / build.rs)
/data/oo_sdk/

# GoldHEN Plugins SDK, cloned + built by the user for tools/ps4-gnm-scrape (task-168)
/data/goldhen_sdk/

# Built homebrew artifacts (examples)
*.pkg
*.elf
*.self
*.bin
eboot.bin

# ...but keep the small prebuilt example ELFs so they run without a rebuild
!examples/**/*.elf

# Sony / proprietary material — never commit
*.pup
*.PUP

# Editor / OS
.idea/
.vscode/
.DS_Store
*.swp

# Dev dumps
full_code.txt

# On-demand GPU state snapshots (task-185): F10/F9 write frame-NNNNN/ directories here
# (override with UNEMUPS4_SNAPSHOT_DIR). Debugging artefacts of one session — never committed.
# GPU state snapshots (task-185). NOT root-anchored on purpose: the dump root defaults
# to a RELATIVE path, so running the emulator from a subdirectory drops the tree there
# instead. An anchored pattern would leave those strays committable.
gpu-snapshots/

# Env-gated guest-module dumps (task-113.2): UNEMUPS4_DUMP_MODULES=<dir> writes each loaded
# module's flat post-relocation image + .map sidecar for offline disassembly. The .bin images
# are already covered by *.bin above, but the .map sidecars are not — ignore the whole default
# dump dir. NOT root-anchored (the dir is a plain, possibly-relative path, like gpu-snapshots).
module-dumps/

# --- agentic-project-template ---

# Logs
logs
*.log

# Editors
!.vscode/extensions.json
*.swo
*.sw?
*~

# Local-only
*.local
.envrc.local

# direnv cache (Nix flake users)
.direnv/

# Skills: .agents/skills/ is vendored (committed). .claude/skills/ holds symlinks into
# it, generated on demand by scripts/skills-bootstrap.sh — not committed.
.claude/skills/

# Stack-specific: Rust build artifacts already ignored above (/target/, **/target/).

# repoctx local index/cache — regenerated on demand, not committed.
.repoctx/

# Local test IWADs (Freedoom etc.) placed under the /app0 mount — runtime fixtures, not source
game_data/**/*.wad
/data/celeste-real-dcb/

# Real-PS4 GNM captures streamed by tools/ps4-gnm-scrape (task-168/198): the receiver's
# default out-dir. Hundreds of MB of command buffers + referenced buffer content dumped
# from a retail title — debugging artefacts derived from the game, never committed.
# NOT root-anchored, like gpu-snapshots/: the out-dir is a plain (possibly relative) path,
# so running the receiver from a subdirectory drops the tree there instead.
dumps/

# Local-only developer files. These are deliberately NOT part of the repo — they are either
# throwaway probes, machine-specific, or contain paths to local retail assets. Ignored rather
# than merely "remembered", so an accidental `git add -A` cannot pick them up. If one of these
# ever becomes worth vendoring, delete its line here first.
/scripts/renderdoc-capture.sh
/crates/gcn/examples/dump_spirv.rs
/crates/gcn/tests/celeste_scope.rs
